<title>GERMANY: Opel recalls Vectra cars to check airbags.</title>
<headline>Opel recalls Vectra cars to check airbags.</headline>
<dateline>RUESSELSHEIM, Germany 1997-05-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Germany's Adam Opel AG, a unit of General Motors Corp, said on Friday it was recalling all its 1300 Opel Vectra model cars due to problems with their door-mounted airbags.</p>
<p>Opel said problems in one vehicle with sensors installed to trigger the airbags had prompted the recall. It added that new sensors could be fitted to other cars within a matter of days.</p>
